	<div class="page-block page-block-text">
			<div class="placeholder-tinymce-text">Dr. Knowlton Video Announcement <a href="https://youtu.be/BPPjLKR_DN4" target="_blank">https://youtu.be/BPPjLKR_DN4</a>
</div>
<div class="placeholder-tinymce-text"><iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/BPPjLKR_DN4" width="560" height="314" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>
<div class="placeholder-tinymce-text"> </div>
<div class="placeholder-tinymce-text"> </div>
<div class="placeholder-tinymce-text">Dr. Knowlton Update 04172020</div>
<div class="placeholder-tinymce-text"> </div>
<div class="placeholder-tinymce-text">
<p class="p1" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px">April 17, 2020</p>
<p class="p2" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px"> </p>
<p class="p3" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px">LISD Parents and Students,</p>
<p class="p4" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px"> </p>
<p class="p3" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px">Earlier today, Governor Greg Abbott announced an executive order to close all schools in the state of Texas for the remainder of the 2019-20 academic year. Lexington ISD, along with all other districts in the state, will comply with this executive order and continue our remote learning that is currently in place for the rest of the school year. <strong>Although our buildings remain closed, students will continue to receive instruction and assignments through our Home-Based Learning platform.</strong></p>
<p class="p3" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px"> </p>
<p class="p3" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px">We know this situation is hard on our students and our staff. <span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>Our students want to return to school and see their friends and classmates. Please know that our teachers and staff are sad too and miss seeing and interacting with our students. As we work through this, remember that we are still together in spirit as our Eagle family and we will all get through this together!</p>
<p class="p4" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px"> </p>
<p class="p3" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px">As we move forward with our instructions and how service to our students and parents, I urge you to communicate with your teachers, counselors and principals.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>They are all working to not only assist with this year’s business, but to also plan appropriately for our students future years at LISD or their next step.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>This is a vital time for your feedback and input.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>Starting next week, our offices at each campus will be opened for phone calls and emails on Monday and Thursday from 8:30-12:30.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>Please reach out with any questions or concerns, and please respond to any communication from the district, the campuses or the teachers. </p>
<p class="p3" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px"> </p>
<p class="p3" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px">This closure is not how any of us wanted to end the school year, and it has created lots of decisions for events and logistics of transitions to another year.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>We are currently working on plans for how we will handle the end of the year activities and the plans for helping students find closure in this school year.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>Please be patient as we find the best solutions for these issues.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>Watch for updates and information coming soon from the district. </p>
<p class="p4" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px"> </p>
<p class="p3" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px">IT’S A GREAT DAY TO BE AN EAGLE!!</p>
<p class="p4" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px"> </p>
<p class="p3" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px">Sincerely,</p>
<p class="p4" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px"> </p>
<p class="p3" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px">Dr. Tonya Knowlton</p>
<p class="p3" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px">LISD Superintendent of Schools</p>
<p class="p4" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px"> </p>
<p class="p3" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px">. </p>
</div>
